Kore Potash intends to raise approximately US$13 million to conduct exploration activities at its  97%-owned Sintoukola Potash Project. This will be done through way of a conditional placing and direct subscriptions of new ordinary shares in the company with certain eligible existing shareholders and new institutional and other investors. Canaccord Genuity and Shore Capital Stockbrokers are acting as joint bookrunners in connection with the placing. Highlights: The net proceeds of the proposed fundraise are expected to be utilised as follows: